## `select()`

::: columns
::: {.column width="30%"}
#### Subset variables

-   by name\
-   by position\
-   by type\
:::

::: {.column width="70%"}
:::{.med-code}

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mcountries %>% 
  select(cntry,
         threatened) %>% 
  head(4)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 4 √ó 2
  cntry     threatened
  <chr>          <int>
1 Indonesia        191
2 Brasil            80
3 China             73
4 Mexico            96
```


:::
:::

:::
:::
:::

## `mutate()`

::: columns
::: {.column width="35%"}
#### Create and modify columns

-   create new\
-   overwrite\
:::

::: {.column width="65%"}

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mcountries %>%
  select(cntry, threatened) %>% 
  mutate(logthreat = log(threatened)) %>% 
  head(5)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 5 √ó 3
  cntry     threatened logthreat
  <chr>          <int>     <dbl>
1 Indonesia        191      5.25
2 Brasil            80      4.38
3 China             73      4.29
4 Mexico            96      4.56
5 Peru              53      3.97
```


:::
:::

:::
:::

We can control where the new column will appear with `.before` and `.after`

## `filter()`


#### Subset rows

Keep only the rows that meet a condition

:::{.med-code}

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mcountries %>% 
  select(cntry, species, threatened) %>% 
  filter(threatened > 75)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
# A tibble: 4 √ó 3
  cntry     species threatened
  <chr>       <int>      <int>
1 Indonesia     670        191
2 Brasil        648         80
3 Mexico        523         96
4 India         412         93
```


:::
:::

:::

## `rename()`


#### Modify column names

New name first  _then_ target column

:::{.med-code}

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mcountries %>% 
  rename(pais=cntry,
         especies=species,
         amenazadas=threatened) %>% 
  head(3)
